/* 
DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS:

This file contains the Firestore indexes required for optimal query performance
in the Liftrix profile system.

MANUAL DEPLOYMENT (Firebase Console):
1. Go to Firebase Console -> Firestore Database -> Indexes
2. Create each composite index manually using the field combinations above
3. Wait for index creation to complete (can take several minutes)

AUTOMATED DEPLOYMENT (Firebase CLI):
1. Install Firebase CLI: npm install -g firebase-tools
2. Initialize Firebase in your project: firebase init firestore
3. Replace the content of firestore.indexes.json with the content above  
4. Deploy indexes: firebase deploy --only firestore:indexes

INDEX USAGE BY FEATURE:

User Search:
- users_public: isPublic + displayName (alphabetical search)
- users_public: isPublic + lastActiveAt (recent activity search)
- user_search_cache: isPublic + searchTokens + lastActiveAt (tokenized search)

Profile System:
- user_achievements: userId + achievementType + unlockedAt (achievement filtering)
- user_achievements: userId + isDisplayed + unlockedAt (displayed achievements)
- profile_images: userId + updatedAt (recent profile images)

QR Code System:
- qr_codes: userId + expiresAt (user's active QR codes)
- qr_codes: expiresAt + createdAt (cleanup expired codes)

Social Features (Future):
- connections: fromUserId + status + createdAt (outgoing connections)
- connections: toUserId + status + createdAt (incoming connections)

PERFORMANCE NOTES:
- Indexes enable sub-100ms query performance for profile operations
- Search queries use cached data to minimize Firestore reads
- Achievement queries are optimized for real-time updates
- Connection queries support pagination for large friend lists

COST OPTIMIZATION:
- Use single-field indexes where possible to reduce storage costs
- Monitor query patterns and remove unused indexes
- Consider query design to minimize index requirements
- Use collection group queries sparingly due to higher costs

MONITORING:
- Set up Firebase Console alerts for slow queries
- Monitor index usage statistics
- Track query costs and optimize frequently-used queries
- Review and update indexes based on usage patterns
*/